comments.body: @escowles could you clarify this question?

This is an updated set of possible values in the existing travel category list (https://github.com/pulibrary/approvals/blob/main/app/models/request.rb#L66). I believe that "Required Business/Teleworkers on-site" and "Education/Training" map to the existing values, and "Acquisitions/Collections" and "Conferences" are new, if that helps avoid doing a data migration to expand this list.

Thanks @escowles. Most of the trips in the system (for IT at least) have been recorded as business travel so if there is a need to filter specifically for teleworkers on site we wouldn't be able to do so on the category value. Is that okay? Or is there a need to filter to just on-site teleworkers in this category?
I don't think there is a need to filter to just on-site teleworkers — that was lumped in with other business travel.

princeton_ansible.title: Switch Alma SFTP Prod and Staging to use Public Key Auth

comments.body:
> We continue to have timeout issues using password authentication and [almasftp@pu.win.princeton.edu](mailto:almasftp@pu.win.princeton.edu) within the Alma environment and lib-sftp-prod1 and lib-sftp-staging1. Alma can give us a public key we can register on each box to use key-based auth instead when connected from the Alma environment. @mzelesky and I gave key-based authentication from Alma a manual test in staging using the Alma sandbox and it worked much faster.
> 
> @kayiwa @acozine a couple of questions?
> 
> 1. Alma can give keys as RSA or ECDSA, should we go with the latter?

the latter.

> 2. Is there a pattern in princeton ansible for managing a public key that we only want to be in the user's authorized_keys files on certain boxes?

look at how we use cdh (that can be expanded) [here](https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/blob/main/playbooks/pulsys_user.yml)

> 3. Are there any concerns with having a user utilize password based authentications in certain contexts (i.e. bibdata/lib-jobs using [almasftp@pu.win.princeton.edu](mailto:almasftp@pu.win.princeton.edu) with a password), but also have the same user configured in the external Alma environment to utilize a public key?

No there aren't.
